criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Female;

          2. Aged of 18 to 40 years;

          3. Conforming to the criteria for the diagnosis of primary dysmenorrhea in the guideline
             developed by Society of Obstetricians and Gynaecologists of Canada（SOGC）in 2017.

          4. With normal menstrual cycle(28±7 days) and normal menstrual period（3-7days）；

          5. Menstrual mean pain score ≥4 on the numerical rating scale (NRS)；

          6. To sign the informed consent and participate in the study voluntarily.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Secondary dysmenorrhea;

          2. Pregnant patients,lactating patients or patients preparing pregnancy.

          3. Subjects with serious heart, liver, kidney damage or cognitive impairment, aphasia,
             mental disorders, or the inability to cooperate with the examination and treatment;

          4. Subjects with coagulation dysfunction or anticoagulants such as warfarin and heparin
             have been used all the time;

          5. Subjects installed with the cardiac pacemaker;

          6. Those who have received relevant acupuncture, transcutaneous electric nerve
             stimulation and other treatment (except pain medication) the last three months;

          7. Patients who may be allergic to electrodes.
